{"lemma":"سَبَحاتُ","slug":"سَبَحاتُ","root":"س.ب.ح","root_slug":"س-ب-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ب-ح","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18666","n18667"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%AD%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"misbaha, rosary"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/sub.ħa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18666","headword_ar":"سَبْحَةٌ","root":"sbH","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Garments of skins:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or, accord. to Sh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sibaAHN","text_ar":"سِبَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is the pl., signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shirts of skins, for boys:"},{"kind":"text","text":"AO corrupted the word, relating it as written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"subojapN","text_ar":"سُبْجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"j","text_ar":"ج"},{"kind":"text","text":", and with damm to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":"; whereas this signifies “ a black [garment of the kind called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisaA='","text_ar":"كِسَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":": ” and a verse cited by him as presenting an ex. of its pl., in its last word, is from a poem of which each verse has for its fundamental rhyme-letter the unpointed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H","text_ar":"ح"},{"kind":"text","text":": ISd, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sbj","text_ar":"سبج"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentions"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sibaAjN","text_ar":"سِبَاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as signifying “ garments of skin, ” and having"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sbjp","text_ar":"سبجة"},{"kind":"text","text":"for its sing.; but says that the word with the unpointed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H","text_ar":"ح"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of higher authority; though he also states it, in the same art., to have been corrupted by AO. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [A meaning belonging to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suboHapN","text_ar":"سُبْحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(q. v.) is assigned in some copies of the K to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboHapN","text_ar":"سَبْحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aboHapu","text_ar":"السَّبْحَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboHapu","text_ar":"سَبْحَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAbiHN","text_ar":"سَابِحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an epithet applied to a horse, or mare, (IAth, TA,) is a proper name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A horse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mare, belonging to the Prophet:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, K, TA:) and of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"another belonging to Jaafar the son of Aboo- Tálib;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) or this was"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mare named"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoHapu","text_ar":"سَمْحَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O:) and of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"another belonging to another."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["K","IAth","TA","O"]},{"entry_id":"n18667","headword_ar":"سُبْحَةٌ","root":"sbH","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Beads"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strung"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon a string"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thread,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ninety-nine in number, and having a mark after each thirtythree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by counting them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one performs the act termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~asobiyH","text_ar":"التَّسْبِيح"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the repetition of the praises of God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"generally consisting in repeating the words"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suboHaAna A@ll~`ho","text_ar":"سُبْحَانَ ا@للّٰهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"thirtythree times,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHamodu lil~`ho","text_ar":"الحَمْدُ لِلّٰهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"thirty-three times, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aall~`hu A^akobaro","text_ar":"اَللّٰهُ اَكْبَرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"thirty-three times, which is done by many persons after the ordinary prayers, as a supererogatory act]: (S, A, Msb, K:) its appellation implies that it is an Arabic word; but Az says that it is post-classical: its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"subaHN","text_ar":"سُبَحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"subuHaAtN","text_ar":"سُبُحَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also. (Har p. 133.) See 2, last sentence but one. ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Invocation of God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supplication:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prayer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whether obligatory"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supererogatory:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supererogatory praise;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supererogatory prayer;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, K;) because of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasobiyHN","text_ar":"تَسْبِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"therein. (Mgh.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN yuSal~iY Als~uboHapa","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يُصَلِّى السُّبْحَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", expl. above; see 2, in the latter part of the paragraph. (Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaDaYsuboHatahu","text_ar":"قَضَىسُبْحَتَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He performed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"finished, his prayer:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaDayotu suboHatiY","text_ar":"قَضَيْتُ سُبْحَتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I performed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"finished, my supererogatory praise"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such prayer."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sal~aY","text_ar":"صَلَّى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~uboHapa","text_ar":"السُّبْحَةَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He performed the supererogatory prayer:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suboHapa AlD~uHaY","text_ar":"سُبْحَةَ الضُّحَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the supererogatory prayer of the period termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~uHaY","text_ar":"الضُّحَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suboHapu A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"سُبْحَةُ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAth, K, TA,) with damm, (TA, [but in my MS. copy of the K written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboHap","text_ar":"سَبْحَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", and so in the CK,]) means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The greatness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"majesty, of God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, K, TA:) or [the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ubuHaAtu","text_ar":"السُّبُحَاتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a trad., means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the greatness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"majesty, and the light"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"splendour"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or by the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"subuHaAtu wajohi","text_ar":"سُبُحَاتُ وَجْهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rab~inaA","text_ar":"رَبِّنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":", is meant (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the greatness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"majesty, of the face of our Lord:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"subuHaAtu wajohi A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"سُبُحَاتُ وَجْهِ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the lights"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"splendours"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (K,) or, accord. to ISh,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the light"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"splendour"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the face of God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, K, TA:) some say that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"subuHaAtu Alwajohi","text_ar":"سُبُحَاتُ الوَجْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the beauties of the face;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because, when you see a person of beautiful face, you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suboHaAna A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"سُبْحَانَ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[to express your admiration]: and some, that [when it relates to God] it denotes a declaration of his being far removed from every imperfection; meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suboHaAna wajohihi","text_ar":"سُبْحَانَ وَجْهِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suboHaAn","text_ar":"سُبْحَان"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) One says, [addressing God,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoA^aluka bisubuHaAti wajohika","text_ar":"اَسْاَلُكَ بِسُبُحَاتِ وَجْهِكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkariymi","text_ar":"الكَرِيمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with two dammehs, meaning (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I ask Thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the evidences of thy greatness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"majesty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the greatness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"majesty, of thy glorious face,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the acknowledgement whereof thy praise is celebrated."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ubuHaAtu","text_ar":"السُّبُحَاتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The places of prostration"},{"kind":"text","text":"[probably meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the reciting of the Kur-án"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.)       -A2-  Also, i. e. [the sing.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suboHapN","text_ar":"سُبْحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A piece of cotton."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","A","IAth","ISh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}